        title: 'Writing: Drafting and Revising',
        text: 'Good writing does not happen in one try. Real writers plan, draft, and revise their work to make it better. In fourth grade, you will write three types of pieces: narratives that tell a story, informational texts that teach about a topic, and opinion pieces that share what you think. Let us learn how to draft and revise each one!',
        culturalHook: 'Think about a time you told a friend about something important. You probably tried different ways to explain it until it made sense — that is what revising is like!',
