          text: 'A narrative tells a story, real or imagined. Good narratives have a clear beginning that introduces characters and the setting. The middle includes a problem or challenge and events that build toward a solution. The ending wraps up the story and often shows what the character learned. Use descriptive details to bring your story to life — describe what characters see, hear, feel, and think. Include dialogue to let characters speak in their own voices. Transition words like "later that day," "suddenly," and "after a while" help the events flow smoothly from one to the next.',
          keyVocabulary: ['narrative', 'dialogue', 'descriptive details', 'transition words'],
